 Both sprains and strains can occur suddenly, such as when you twist your ankle or knee, or gradually, such as when you overuse a muscle or joint over time.
 Symptoms of sprains and strains can include pain, swelling, bruising, limited mobility, and difficulty moving the affected joint or muscle.
 Treatment for sprains and strains often involves rest, ice, compression, and elevation (RICE) to reduce pain and inflammation. You may also need to use physical therapy or exercise to help strengthen the affected muscle or joint and improve its range of motion.
